{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014gMxHfbihBSzVewekYaift","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.addressbook.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.Date;\n     5→\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.GenerationType;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.Temporal;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.TemporalType;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ *\n    15→ * @author ian\n    16→ */\n    17→@Entity\n    18→public class Contact implements Serializable {\n    19→\n    20→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -825634229676522580L;\n    21→    @Id\n    22→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.AUTO)\n    23→    private Long id;\n    24→    protected String firstName;\n    25→    protected String lastName;\n    26→    protected String email;\n    27→    protected String mobilePhone;\n    28→    protected String homePhone;\n    29→    @Temporal(TemporalType.DATE)\n    30→    protected Date birthday;\n    31→\n    32→    /**\n    33→     * Get the value of birthday\n    34→     *\n    35→     * @return the value of birthday\n    36→     */\n    37→    public Date getBirthday() {\n    38→        return birthday;\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    /**\n    42→     * Set the value of birthday\n    43→     *\n    44→     * @param birthday new value of birthday\n    45→     */\n    46→    public void setBirthday(Date birthday) {\n    47→        this.birthday = birthday;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    /**\n    51→     * Get the value of homePhone\n    52→     *\n    53→     * @return the value of homePhone\n    54→     */\n    55→    public String getHomePhone() {\n    56→        return homePhone;\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    /**\n    60→     * Set the value of homePhone\n    61→     *\n    62→     * @param homePhone new value of homePhone\n    63→     */\n    64→    public void setHomePhone(String homePhone) {\n    65→        this.homePhone = homePhone;\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    /**\n    69→     * Get the value of mobilePhone\n    70→     *\n    71→     * @return the value of mobilePhone\n    72→     */\n    73→    public String getMobilePhone() {\n    74→        return mobilePhone;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    /**\n    78→     * Set the value of mobilePhone\n    79→     *\n    80→     * @param mobilePhone new value of mobilePhone\n    81→     */\n    82→    public void setMobilePhone(String mobilePhone) {\n    83→        this.mobilePhone = mobilePhone;\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    /**\n    87→     * Get the value of email\n    88→     *\n    89→     * @return the value of email\n    90→     */\n    91→    public String getEmail() {\n    92→        return email;\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    /**\n    96→     * Set the value of email\n    97→     *\n    98→     * @param email new value of email\n    99→     */\n   100→    public void setEmail(String email) {\n   101→        this.email = email;\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    /**\n   105→     * Get the value of lastName\n   106→     *\n   107→     * @return the value of lastName\n   108→     */\n   109→    public String getLastName() {\n   110→        return lastName;\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    /**\n   114→     * Set the value of lastName\n   115→     *\n   116→     * @param lastName new value of lastName\n   117→     */\n   118→    public void setLastName(String lastName) {\n   119→        this.lastName = lastName;\n   120→    }\n   121→\n   122→    /**\n   123→     * Get the value of firstName\n   124→     *\n   125→     * @return the value of firstName\n   126→     */\n   127→    public String getFirstName() {\n   128→        return firstName;\n   129→    }\n   130→\n   131→    /**\n   132→     * Set the value of firstName\n   133→     *\n   134→     * @param firstName new value of firstName\n   135→     */\n   136→    public void setFirstName(String firstName) {\n   137→        this.firstName = firstName;\n   138→    }\n   139→\n   140→    public Long getId() {\n   141→        return id;\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    public void setId(Long id) {\n   145→        this.id = id;\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    @Override\n   149→    public int hashCode() {\n   150→        int hash = 0;\n   151→        hash += (id != null ? id.hashCode() : 0);\n   152→        return hash;\n   153→    }\n   154→\n   155→    @Override\n   156→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   157→        // TODO: Warning - this method won't work in the case the id fields are not set\n   158→        if (!(object instanceof Contact)) {\n   159→            return false;\n   160→        }\n   161→        Contact other = (Contact) object;\n   162→        if ((this.id == null && other.id != null) || (this.id != null && !this.id.equals(other.id))) {\n   163→            return false;\n   164→        }\n   165→        return true;\n   166→    }\n   167→\n   168→    @Override\n   169→    public String toString() {\n   170→        return \"addressbook.entity.Contact[id=\" + id + \"]\";\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→}\n   174→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012QZR1m2eWYrGiba9RfCZPw","session_id":"fd257968-fc09-4865-84ad-86d17cc4ff85","uuid":"3c391596-0d40-42a2-8bc1-a1076710f376"}
