{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TZxByRaZpMfAymR3fwRKNt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→package quarkus.tutorial.addressbook.ejb;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.List;\n    15→\n    16→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    17→import jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    18→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\n    19→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\n    20→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Root;\n    21→\n    22→/**\n    23→ *\n    24→ * @author ian\n    25→ */\n    26→public abstract class AbstractFacade<T> {\n    27→\n    28→    private final Class<T> entityClass;\n    29→\n    30→    protected AbstractFacade(Class<T> entityClass) {\n    31→        this.entityClass = entityClass;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    protected abstract EntityManager getEntityManager();\n    35→\n    36→    public void create(T entity) {\n    37→        getEntityManager().persist(entity);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public void edit(T entity) {\n    41→        getEntityManager().merge(entity);\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    public void remove(T entity) {\n    45→        getEntityManager().remove(getEntityManager().merge(entity));\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public T find(Object id) {\n    49→        return getEntityManager().find(entityClass, id);\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    public List<T> findAll() {\n    53→        CriteriaBuilder cb = getEntityManager().getCriteriaBuilder();\n    54→        CriteriaQuery<T> cq = cb.createQuery(entityClass);\n    55→        cq.select(cq.from(entityClass));\n    56→        TypedQuery<T> q = getEntityManager().createQuery(cq);\n    57→        return q.getResultList();\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    public List<T> findRange(int[] range) {\n    61→        CriteriaBuilder cb = getEntityManager().getCriteriaBuilder();\n    62→        CriteriaQuery<T> cq = cb.createQuery(entityClass);\n    63→        cq.select(cq.from(entityClass));\n    64→        TypedQuery<T> q = getEntityManager().createQuery(cq);\n    65→        // keep your current (exclusive upper bound) behavior:\n    66→        q.setMaxResults(range[1] - range[0]);\n    67→        q.setFirstResult(range[0]);\n    68→        return q.getResultList();\n    69→    }\n    70→\n    71→    public int count() {\n    72→        CriteriaBuilder cb = getEntityManager().getCriteriaBuilder();\n    73→        CriteriaQuery<Long> cq = cb.createQuery(Long.class);\n    74→        Root<T> rt = cq.from(entityClass);\n    75→        cq.select(cb.count(rt));\n    76→        return getEntityManager().createQuery(cq).getSingleResult().intValue();\n    77→    }\n    78→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012QZR1m2eWYrGiba9RfCZPw","session_id":"fd257968-fc09-4865-84ad-86d17cc4ff85","uuid":"c893caae-22c2-4765-9a94-bf76825d8bfd"}
