{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":1025223,"duration_api_ms":731562,"num_turns":78,"result":"---\n\n## Migration Summary\n\n**Frameworks:** Quarkus 3.30.5 -> Spring Boot 3.2.5\n\n**Overall Outcome:** SUCCESS - All 11 smoke tests passed, 0 failures.\n\n### High-level Actions Performed\n1. Analyzed Quarkus + JSF address book application with JPA/Hibernate/H2\n2. Rewrote `pom.xml` replacing all Quarkus dependencies with Spring Boot starters\n3. Created Spring Boot application entry point (`@SpringBootApplication`)\n4. Migrated `Contact` JPA entity (preserved Jakarta Persistence annotations)\n5. Replaced EJB-style `AbstractFacade`/`ContactFacade` with Spring Data JPA `ContactRepository`\n6. Created REST controller (`/api/contacts`) and web controller (`/contacts`) replacing JSF `ContactController`\n7. Created Thymeleaf HTML templates replacing JSF XHTML views\n8. Migrated `application.properties` from Quarkus to Spring Boot format\n9. Updated `Dockerfile` for Spring Boot fat JAR execution\n10. Removed all obsolete Quarkus/JSF files\n\n### File Tree\n\n```\nModified:\n- pom.xml: Replaced Quarkus BOM/dependencies with Spring Boot 3.2.5 parent and starters\n- src/main/resources/application.properties: Migrated from Quarkus to Spring Boot config syntax\n- Dockerfile: Changed build (mvn package) and run (java -jar) commands for Spring Boot\n\nAdded:\n- smoke.py: 11 smoke tests covering CRUD operations via REST API\n- CHANGELOG.md: Full migration documentation\n- src/main/java/com/example/addressbook/AddressBookApplication.java: Spring Boot entry point\n- src/main/java/com/example/addressbook/entity/Contact.java: JPA entity (migrated package)\n- src/main/java/com/example/addressbook/repository/ContactRepository.java: Spring Data JPA repository\n- src/main/java/com/example/addressbook/controller/ContactRestController.java: REST API controller\n- src/main/java/com/example/addressbook/controller/ContactWebController.java: Web (Thymeleaf) controll